Here's TUnit's lifecycle at each scope:

## 1. Before/After every individual test

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // runs after each test
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_IsValid() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 2. Once before first / after last test in a class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task OpenFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // static — runs once before any test in this class
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once after all tests in this class finish
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_IsValid() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 3. Once per assembly (before/after all tests in the assembly)

```csharp
public class WireMockHook
{
    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once before any test in the assembly
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once after all assembly tests complete
    }
}
```

## 4. Once for the entire test session (global start/end)

```csharp
public class GlobalDatabaseHook
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        // very first thing that runs
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDownDatabase(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        // very last thing that runs
    }
}
```

---

**Key points:**

| Scope | Attribute | Method must be |
|-------|-----------|----------------|
| Test | `[Before(Test)]` / `[After(Test)]` | Instance |
| Class | `[Before(Class)]` / `[After(Class)]` | **Static** |
| Assembly | `[Before(Assembly)]` / `[After(Assembly)]` | **Static** |
| Session | `[Before(TestSession)]` / `[After(TestSession)]` | **Static** |

**Bonus:** Use `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` (static, on any class) for a *global* cross-cutting hook that fires for every test regardless of class — handy for logging or diagnostics. The `Class`/`Assembly` variants exist too.

All hooks can be `async Task` and optionally accept a `CancellationToken` as a second parameter.
